Emmanuel Onani  The Inspector General of Police (IGP), Mr. Mohammed Adamu, has accused the Islamic Movement of Nigeria (IMN) of plotting to enthrone an Islamic state in the country. He said the Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky-led IMN was engaging in a campaign of “extreme radicalism and terrorism” against the state, to further its alleged agenda. Adamu, who spoke at the on-going conference of senior police officers, vowed the readiness of the Force to crush further violent protests by members of the group. A Federal High Court in Abuja Friday, made an order proscribing the activities of the IMN. Details later…